Bank 1 -- * Client
A Client has A Bank. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one Bank.
A Bank has some Clients. It can have none, and there is no upper bound defined.
When a Client is created, its Bank must be assigned. When a Client is deleted, its Bank is not deleted and its list of Clients is decreased. When a Bank is deleted, its Clients are not deleted. They are assigned to another Bank.
